  "description": "<p>\n\t&nbsp;&nbsp;<img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201505/4b1e75ac637245f986d8dcced68be4f9.jpg\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">在记忆和背诵考研单词时，老师们会推荐词根词缀法记忆单词，这种方法科学合理，记忆牢固并且迅速。同时，我们都知道，词汇的前缀一般修饰或者改变单词的意思，词汇的后缀一般改变单词的词性。为了广大考生更好更快的记忆单词，对考研英语词汇常见后缀进行了汇总，希望对2016届考研的广大考生有所帮助。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong><span style=\"color: #b22222;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">1. -ese：</span></span></strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Chin(a) + ese&rarr;Chinese n. 中国人；汉语</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">E.g. Remember you are a Chinese wherever you go.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">不论你到哪里，记住你是中国人。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Japan + ese&rarr;Japanese n. 日本人；日语</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">E.g. Not only did he speak English well, but he spoke Japanese more easily.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">他不但英语说得好，就连日语也讲得轻松自如。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong><span style=\"color: #b22222;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">2. -(r)ess：</span></span></strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">host+ ess&rarr;hostess n. 女主人</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">E.g. The hostess gave us a cordial greeting.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">女主人热忱地欢迎我们。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">act+ ress&rarr;actress n. 女演员</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">E.g. The famous actress is now appearing at the Capital Theatre.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">目前这位著名女演员正在首都剧场演出。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong><span style=\"color: #b22222;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">3. -ian：</span></span></strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">logic+ ian&rarr;logician n. 逻辑学家</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">E.g. As the founder of pragmatism, firstly and mostly Peirce was a logician.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">作为实用主义的鼻祖，皮尔士首先和主要是一位逻辑学家。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">mathematic+ ian&rarr;mathematician n. 数学家</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">E.g. Einstein is identified with a higher mathematician.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">爱因斯坦被列为高等数学家。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong><span style=\"color: #b22222;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">4.-ist：</span></span></strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">drama+ (t)ist&rarr;dramatist n. 剧作家</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">E.g. Shakespeare is, by common consent, the greatest English dramatist.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">莎士比亚被公认是英国最伟大的剧作家。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">dent+ ist&rarr;dentist n. 牙科医生</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">E.g. The dentist told the boy not to eat too many sweets.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">牙医告诫这男孩不要吃太多糖果。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong><span style=\"color: #b22222;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">5.-ster：</span></span></strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">young+ ster&rarr;youngster n. 年轻人</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">E.g. That youngster works with a will.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">这小伙子干活有股傻劲儿。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">gang+ ster&rarr;gangster n. 歹徒</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">E.g. The police are hard on the track of the gangster.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">警察正在追踪那名匪徒。</span></p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p731860/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p731860\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li styl